    TODO()
}

// Gathers a quorum of nodes (a node might include itself into a quorum)
// and asks the quorum for the highest index they have seen
// (promised or accepted), regardless of whether they know
// it is fully committed yet

// if a node, during a read operation, asks a quorum (the node itself can be part of the quorum)
// "What is the highest slot you have seen any activity for (Promised or Accepted)?",
// is it actually enough to not return stale data?

// Gemini: Yes, it is absolutely enough to guarantee you will not return stale data.
// In fact, this is the exact mathematical foundation that
// allows leaderless consensus protocols to support strict
// linearizability (strong consistency).
getHighestQuorumKnownSlot() {
    TODO()
}

getHighestKnownSlot() {
    return highest_known_slot
}

